      "description": "<p><strong>Max Ranks</strong>: 5</p><p>A Confused creature has difficulty distinguishing friend from foe and experiences lapsing judgement.</p><ul><li><p>A Confused creature suffers a -1 penalty to all Wisdom based checks, attack rolls, and saving throws for each rank it has.</p></li><li><p>A Confused creature who would target hostile or friendly creature with an attack, jutsu, feature or trait (even themselves) must first make a DC 8 Flat check. On a failure, they must target the closest creature to them, ignoring allied or hostile distinctions. For rank of Confused beyond the first, increase this DC by +1 (Max DC 12).</p></li><li><p>A Confused creature cannot choose targets when a jutsu, feature or trait would allow them to pick. All creatures in range become the target, ignoring ally or hostile distinctions.</p></li><li><p>As an Action, a Confused creature can make a DC 15 Intelligence ability check, ending this condition on a success.</p></li></ul>",
      "tint": "#ffffff",
